This paper focuses on the design and implementation of GraphQL interfaces, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The paper also analyzes the schemas of GraphQL APIs, which involves data management and storage (cs.DB) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper discusses security concerns related to complex queries, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses ways in which GraphQL APIs attempt to address these concerns, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
